definition.value: A type of dietary survey method that is based on a recall of food or drink intake that have already been consumed.
A type of dietary survey method that involves recording the diet when the foods or drinks are being consumed.

label.value: retrospective method for assessing dietary diversity

definition.value: A retrospective dietary survey method that provides a score that represents a number of different foods, drinks and/or food groups consumed over a given reference period.

A type of retrospective dietary survey method where respondents are asked, by a nutritionist or dietitian who has been trained in interviewing techniques, to recall and report all foods and beverages consumed over the preceding 24 hours.
A type of retrospective dietary survey method that is a detailed assessment to describe usual food intake and its variation over a long period of time.

A retrospective dietary survey method that assesses the frequency with which foods and/or food groups are eaten over a certain time period. The questionnaire includes a food list (commonly close-ended), a frequency category section, and can be self- or interviewer administered.

A type of prospective dietary survey method that involves setting aside duplicate portions of all foods and beverages consumed throughout a specific time period. These duplicate portions are set aside, weighed, either by the respondent or fieldworker, and then sent to a laboratory for chemical analysis to determine content.
A type of prospective dietary survey method collecting data about the foods and beverages consumed over a previously specified period of time.

label.value: retrospective method for assessing dietary diversity of infant and yong child

definition.value: A retrospective method for assessing dietary diversity with the "Infant and Young Child Dietary Diversity Score" (IYCDDS, defined as the Proportion of children 6–23 months of age who receive foods from four or more predefined food groups.

label.value: retrospective method for assessing dietary diversity of women

definition.value: A retrospective method for assessing dietary diversity in women. Minimum Dietary Diversity-Women is a dichotomous indicator of whether or not women of 15–49 years of age have consumed at least five out of ten predefined food groups during the previous 24 hours.
A retrospective dietary survey method that uses modified versions of longer Food Frequency Questionnaires varying in length, frequency categories and number of foods listed.
A type of Food Frequency Questionnaire method that collects only frequency of food or drink intake.
A type of Food Frequency Questionnaire method that includes information about both the frequency and quantity of food or drink intake.

A type of dietary records method that adopts the same methodological principles as the estimated food record method. However, in this method respondents are asked to weigh foods or drinks using weighing scales.
A type of dietary records method that instructions respondents to document all foods and beverages consumed during a predefined period.

label.value: quality indicator of a dietary survey

definition.value: An information content entity that specifies the quality of a dietary survey.

label.value: quality indicator of a diet recall method

definition.value: : An indicator that specifies the quality of a diet recall method.

label.value: quality indicator of a diet survey questionnaire

definition.value: An indicator that specifies the quality of dietary survey questionnaires that includes a predetermined set of questions used to collect diet intake information.

label.value: representativeness of days as a quality indicator of a dietary survey

definition.value: An indicator that specifies the representativeness of days of a dietary survey.

label.value: quality indicator of a food quantification method

definition.value: An indicator that specifies the accuracy of a food quantification process (i.e. a process that helps express food intake into units of weights or volume.).

label.value: administration type of a diet recall method

definition.value: An indicator that specifies the administration type of a diet recall method. A diet recall method can be proxy administered, self-administered or interview administered.
An indicator that specifies when the dietary intake was recorded. (e.g. during eating occasion, immediately after eating occasion, or later).

label.value: origin of a diet survey questionnaire

definition.value: An indicator that specifies how the questionnaire was developed (e.g. de novo self-developed questionnaire, standardized questionnaire, questionnaire adapted from another questionnaires, etc.).

label.value: content validity of a diet survey questionnaire

definition.value: An indicator that specifies the content validity of a diet survey questionnaire in another comparable population in terms of both age and dietary habits. The reference, the type of the validation, and validation estimates are important pieces of information.

label.value: representativeness of seasons of a dietary survey

definition.value: An indicator that specifies if data collection was seasonality representative.

label.value: representativeness of week/weekend days of a dietary survey

definition.value: An indicator that specifies the representativeness of week/weekend days when conducting a dietary survey.

label.value: number of days of a dietary survey

definition.value: An indicator that specifies the number of days of a dietary recall/measurement per individual.

label.value: selection of recall/measurement days of a dietary survey

definition.value: An indicator that specifies how the recall/measurement days of a dietary survey were selected.

label.value: quantification of a food portion size

definition.value: An indicator that specifies how the quantity of the portion sizes is estimated.
An indicator that specifies how food intake data are expressed into units of weights or volume.
An indicator for food quantification method that indicates whether a food quantification method is geography matched to the area where the food is estimated.
An indicator for food quantification method that indicates whether a food quantification method is tailored to the characteristics of the assessed population.

label.value: referred food composition data for quantification

definition.value: An indicator that indicates how the measured food intake data are matched to food composition data.

label.value: abstract of a published study based on dietary survey(s)

definition.value: An abstract which states the dietary/nutritional assessment method(s) used in the research (STROBE-nut-1).
A results section that reports the number of individuals excluded based on missing, incomplete or implausible dietary/nutritional data.

label.value: methods of a published study based on dietary survey(s)

definition.value: a methods section that includes a few sections to describe particular characterisitics of study methods based on dietary surveys.

label.value: results section of a published study based on dietary survey(s)

definition.value: A results section that includes a few sections to describe particular characterisitics of research results of a study based on dietary surveys.

label.value: discussion of a published study based on dietary survey(s)

definition.value: A discussion section that interprets particular characterisitics of a study based on dietary surveys.

label.value: ethics of a published study based on dietary survey(s)

definition.value: an ethical approval section that describes the procedure for consent and study approval from ethics committee(s).
A discussion section that describes the main limitations of the data sources and assessment methods used and implications for the interpretation of the findings.

label.value: supplementary material of a published study based on dietary survey(s)

definition.value: a supplementary (online) material that provides data collection tools and data as online material or explain how they can be accessed.
A methods section that describes any characteristics of the study settings that might affect the dietary intake or nutritional status of the participants, if applicable.
A methods section that reports particular dietary, physiological or nutritional characteristics that were considered when selecting the target population.

A methods section that a) clearly defines foods, food groups, nutrients, or other food components.b) when using dietary patterns or indices, describes the methods to obtain them and their nutritional properties.
A methods section that includes 6 elements for the description of data measurements of a study based on dietary survey(s).
A method section that reports how bias in dietary or nutritional assessment was addressed, e.g., misreporting, changes in habits as a result of being measured, or data imputation from other sources
A methods section that explains categorization of dietary/nutritional data (e.g., use of N-tiles and handling of nonconsumers) and the choice of reference category, if applicable.

label.value: statistical analysis section of a published study based on dietary survey(s)

definition.value: A statistical analysis section that a) describes any statistical method used to combine dietary or nutritional data, if applicable; b) describes and justifies the method for energy adjustments, intake modeling, and use of weighting factors, if applicable; c) reports any adjustments for measurement error, i.e,. from a validity or calibration study.

A data measurements section that describes the dietary assessment method(s), e.g., portion size estimation, number of days and items recorded, how it was developed and administered, and how quality was assured, and report if and how supplement intake was assessed.

A data measurements section that describes and justifies food composition data used. (e.g. explain the procedure to match food composition with consumption data and describe the use of conversion factors, if applicable.)
